.TH "ocs_aes_ccm_op" 9 "ocs_aes_ccm_op" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ocs_aes_ccm_op \- Perform CCM operation.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ocs_aes_ccm_op
.BI "(struct ocs_aes_dev *aes_dev "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_cipher cipher "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_instruction instruction "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t dst_dma_list "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t src_dma_list "  ","
.BI "u32 src_size "  ","
.BI "u8 *iv "  ","
.BI "dma_addr_t adata_dma_list "  ","
.BI "u32 adata_size "  ","
.BI "u8 *in_tag "  ","
.BI "u32 tag_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aes_dev" 12
The OCS AES device to use.
.IP "cipher" 12
The Cipher to use (AES or SM4).
.IP "instruction" 12
The instruction to perform (encrypt or decrypt).
.IP "dst_dma_list" 12
The OCS DMA list mapping output memory.
.IP "src_dma_list" 12
The OCS DMA list mapping input payload data.
.IP "src_size" 12
The amount of data mapped by \fIsrc_dma_list\fP.
.IP "iv" 12
The input IV vector.
.IP "adata_dma_list" 12
The OCS DMA list mapping input A-data.
.IP "adata_size" 12
The amount of data mapped by \fIadata_dma_list\fP.
.IP "in_tag" 12
Input tag.
.IP "tag_size" 12
The size (in bytes) of \fIin_tag\fP.
.SH "NOTE"
for encrypt the tag is appended to the ciphertext (in the memory
mapped by \fIdst_dma_list\fP).
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
